The title of '''Surface Marshal''', or '''Surface Marshall''', and alternatively named as '''Army Sector Commander''', and simply '''Marshall''', was used by the [[Commander/Legends|commander]] of a [[sector army]]; the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]] forces within a [[Sector Group/Legends|Sector Group]]. Usually, it was merely another titled bestowed onto the [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] or [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] who commanded the Sector Group.<ref name="Imperial Sourcebook" /> During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]], Marshall [[VeNiste]] served as the Army Sector Commander of the [[Trans-Nebular sector/Legends|Trans-Nebular sector]], and dispatched a communique to Imperial forces on [[Goroth Prime]] that [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/LN starfighters]] were subordinate to [[General/Legends|General]] [[Anderton Kloff]] when stationed [[Planet/Legends|planetside]], an order [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Val DeGoort]] ordered his forces to obey.<ref name="Goroth">''[[Goroth: Slave of the Empire]]''</ref>
{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The title of Surface Marshal was introduced in the ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''; the same publication shows a rank plaque for a Priority Sector High Commander, which corresponds to the badge worn by Grand Moff [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], except for a lack of code cylinders. This may have been the insignia of the Surface Marshal/High Admiral of an [[Oversector/Legends|Oversector]].

